  <section class="recipes container">
    <article class="row">
      <div class="col-sm-10 col-sm-push-1">
        <header>
          <h1 class="text-center">Mac & Cheese</h1>
        </header>
        <figure>
          <img src="http://mtltimes.ca/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/mac-and-cheese.jpg" alt="macaroni and cheese"/>
        </figure>
        <p class="lead">Your family will fall in love with homemade mac and cheese all over again. Trust us, this ooey-gooey oven bake is cheesier than you ever thought possible</p>
        <section class="ingredients">
          <h2>Ingredients</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>3 Tbsp. non-hydrogenated margarine</li>
            <li>1/4 cup flour</li>
            <li>2 cups milk</li>
            <li>1/4 cup Kraft 100% Parmesan Grated Cheese</li>
            <li>2 cups Cracker Barrel Shredded Old Cheddar Cheese, divided</li>
            <li>1-3/4 cups elbow macaroni, cooked</li>
            <li>1/4 cup fresh bread crumbs</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
        <section class="directions">
          <h2>Directions</h2>
          <ol>
            <li>Heat oven to 350Â°F.</li>
            <li>Melt margarine in large saucepan on medium heat. Whisk in flour; cook 1 min., stirring constantly. Gradually stir in milk; cook and stir 3 to 5 min. or until thickened. Add Parmesan and 1-1/2 cups cheddar; cook and stir 1 min. or until cheddar is melted. Add macaroni; stir to evenly coat.</li>
            <li>Spoon into 1.5-L casserole dish sprayed with cooking spray; top with remaining cheddar, then bread crumbs.</li>
            <li>Bake 20 min. or until macaroni mixture is heated through and topping is lightly browned.</li>
          </ol>
        </section>
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>
</main>




